For the tree drawn above,inordergives:1 3 4 6 7 8 10 13 14. That’s not a coincidence —inorder
traversal of a Binary Search Tree always gives sorted order(more in 3.3).
Level-order traversal(a.k.a. Breadth-First Search on a tree) visits level by level, left to right — this one is
NOT naturally recursive; it needs a queue:
#define MAXQ1000
voidlevelOrder(structTreeNode*root){
if(root==NULL)return;
