Why does worst case degrade to O(n)?If you insert already-sorted data (1, 2, 3, 4, 5...), the BST becomes
a straight line — effectively a linked list. This is exactly the problem AVL trees solve next.
3.4 AVL Trees — self-balancing BSTs
An AVL tree is a BST that automatically keeps itself balanced, guaranteeing O(log n) for every operation
— no worst-case O(n) degradation. It does this by tracking abalance factorat every node:height(left
subtree) - height(right subtree). If that ever becomes -2 or +2 after an insertion, the tree performs
a
rotation
to fix itself.
