5.2 Binary Search
Requiressorteddata, but in exchange gives O(log n) — repeatedly halve the search space by comparing
against the middle element.
intbinarySearch(intarr[],intn,inttarget){
intlow=0,high=n-1;
while(low<=high){
intmid=low+(high-low)/2;// NOT (low + high) / 2 — avoids integer overflow
if(arr[mid]==target)returnmid;
elseif(arr[mid]<target)low=mid+1;
elsehigh=mid-1;
}
return-1;
}
That overflow comment is worth remembering:(low + high) / 2can overflow iflowandhighare both
large, even though neither alone would.low + (high - low) / 2gives the identical result without that
risk — a small detail interviewers sometimes specifically probe for.
Recursive version(same logic, useful if asked for both):
