Prim’sAlgorithmsolves the same MST problem with a different strategy — grow a single tree one edge at a
time, always adding the cheapest edge that connects a new vertex to the tree. It’s structurally very similar to
Dijkstra (both repeatedly pick a “closest” vertex), except Prim’s compares edge weights directly rather than
accumulated path distance. Worth knowing the distinction if asked to compare them, even without writing
the full code.
